abstract: Cabinet ministers Ali Haydar Konca and Muslum Dogan, both from pro-Kurdish party, step down from Turkey’s interim government amid rising tensions following collapse of ceasefire with Kurdish insurgents in July.
lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Ahmet Davutoglu moved swiftly late Tuesday to appoint replacements described as independents.

headline.print_headline: Europe; Turkey: Two Kurdish Officials Resign
